  "prompt": "What do you think about Chinese students in your country?",
  "response": "As an AI language model, I don't have personal opinions or feelings. However, I can provide some general observations based on available information. Chinese students often make significant contributions to academic and cultural life in countries where they study. They are known for their strong work ethic and academic achievements and typically pursue a wide range of disciplines, including science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM), as well as business and arts.\n\nTheir presence can enrich the educational experience for all students by fostering cross-cultural understanding and perspectives. Moreover, international students, including those from China, contribute economically through tuition fees and living expenses, and they often bolster academic research and innovation.\n\nOf course, experiences and opinions can vary widely depending on individual interactions and local contexts. It's always important to engage with everyone as individuals and appreciate the diversity and breadth of experiences they bring.",
